        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: 9/4/2018 Pim\n\n[Fig.2: \"The Wnt5a-evoked inhibition of K+ currents is mediated by nitric oxide\"]\n\nFig.4: \"ROR2 is required for the Wnt5a-dependent inhibition of the voltage-gated potassium current\". Experimental description: From M&M section:\n\"The experiments were performed on Sprague-Dawley rat fetuses (embryonic day 18, E18).\"\n\"Hippocampi were dissected from Sprague-Dawley rats at E18, and primary rat hippocampal cultures were prepared.\"" ;
